{
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The recording we’ll be working with today is from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "url": "https://hrc.contentdm.oclc.org/digital/collection/p15878coll1/id/37/rec/1",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "“‘Criminal Syndicalism’ case, McComb, Mississippi (Side 1)”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " recording from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "url": "https://hrc.contentdm.oclc.org/digital/collection/p15878coll1",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "John Beecher Sound Recordings Collection"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " at the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "url": "https://www.hrc.utexas.edu/",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "University of Texas’s Harry Ransom Center"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ". This recording was recorded on October 19, 1964 by John Beecher and his wife, Barbara. The recording begins with John Beecher, a writer and activist, and members of the Council of Federated Organizations (COFO) meeting with Black high school students and their parents after these students were released from jail in McComb, Mississippi on charges of criminal syndicalism, in which the students have been falsely accused of damaging property by throwing a brick."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In the lesson, we're going to be listening to two clips: one where a member of the COFO is speaking to students about the charges they faced and the importance of voting before they begin asking them about their experiences (from :11-4:15), and the other where Beecher asks the students if they had recreational privileges while in jail and some of the conditions they faced (from 14:07-15:37)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Please note: ",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "You will hear real people describing traumatic events from their lives in response to direct questioning. While the clip selected for this lesson does not include all sensitive content from the full recording, you will hear:"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulleted-list",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Descriptions of arrest, incarceration, and the criminal justice system"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "An outdated term (\"negro\") used by one speaker to describe Black people"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Moments where speakers describe feeling dehumanized and targeted by authorities"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "You have options for how to engage with this material. If at any point you feel uncomfortable, please let your instructor know."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Now, listen to BOTH lesson clips below. Respond in your instructor's preferred style (handwritten, voice memo, etc.) to the following prompts:",
          "bold": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "bulleted-list",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Share one thing you noticed about each clip."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "list-item",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Share one thing you wondered about each clip."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
